   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Operate the lift, tilt and attachment controls. Listen for
unusual noises. These may indicate a need for repair.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check for loose bolts and nuts on the carriage. Remove any
debris from the carriage and mast.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check the forks and attachments for free operation and damage. Have repairs made if
          necessary.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <fig id="fig_yrw_fxz_5gc" class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="media/image1140.png"
                         id="image_asw_fxz_5gc"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
               <p class="- topic/p ">Typical Example</p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Brush a film of oil on all links of the chain.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Raise and lower the carriage a few times to allow lubricant to enter into the chain
          links.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <note type="warning" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Lubricate chains more frequently than normal in applications where the lift truck is
            operating in an atmosphere which could cause corrosion of components or when lift truck
            must work in rapid lift cycles.</p>
               </note>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Check the air cleaner housing for loose latches.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
